metadata.title: Landing on the Moon
metadata.description: Successful Moon lander and impactor missions, by country
metadata.main_insight: The United States has the most successful lunar landing and impactor missions, followed by the USSR/Russia and China. The chart distinguishes between lander and impactor missions.

datafacts.annotation: The Units of Lander and Total show a positive correlation.
datafacts.reason: The Pearson correlation coefficient of the Units between Lander and Total is {r:.2f}, indicating a strong positive relationship.

datafacts.annotation: The Impactor shows a sudden jump in Units from India to United States.
datafacts.reason: The Units for Impactor increases from 1 at India to 4 at United States, indicating a sharp change.

datafacts.annotation: The Lander, Total all have the largest proportion in China.
datafacts.reason: The Units of Lander, Total in China all account for 0.42857142857142855, larger than all other Mission Type, of the total of Units of all Mission Type.

datafacts.annotation: The Total has the largest proportion in United States.
datafacts.reason: The Units of Total in United States accounts for 0.5, larger than all other Mission Type, of the total of Units of all Mission Type.

datafacts.annotation: The Total has the largest proportion in USSR.
datafacts.reason: The Units of Total in USSR accounts for 0.5, larger than all other Mission Type, of the total of Units of all Mission Type.
